{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","data":{"alias":"decisive-anarthrous-oryx","description":"# op-cert: AWS IaC + deploy of the trusted gate service + live authenticated integrity test\n\n## Why\nThe trusted gate service (the sibling service story) is only a trust anchor once it runs in an\nisolated environment whose key nobody else can read. This story declares that environment as\ncode, **actually deploys it** (an authenticated AWS CLI is provided — the deploy is in scope, not\nmerely declared), and proves the deployed endpoint end-to-end. Deployment decisions are settled in\nthe epic's \"Producer-signing & compute-runtime design resolution\": **ECS Fargate** (long-lived\nservice; Lambda rejected — 15-min ceiling + API Gateway sync timeout vs 30s–minutes gate runs)\nbehind **API Gateway (HTTP API) with IAM SigV4 auth**, deliberately NOT the shared review-bot\ncompose VM (the signing key warrants an isolated runtime whose task role reads exactly one\nsecret).\n\n## What\nTerraform under `infra/opcert/`:\n- **API Gateway HTTP API** with an **IAM (SigV4) authorizer**, invoke permission restricted to a\n  named admin role, TLS only; routes proxied to the Fargate service.\n- **ECS Fargate service** (desired_count=1) running the image from\n  `infra/compose/Dockerfile.opcert` (pushed to ECR), with the service's env\n  (`REBAR_OPCERT_ENV_ID`, secret ARNs, remote URLs) in the task definition.\n- **AWS Secrets Manager** secret holding the **passphrase-free Ed25519 private key**, encrypted at\n  rest by a **KMS CMK**. Server-side SSHSIG signing — **NOT AWS KMS managed signing** (KMS\n  asymmetric SIGN_VERIFY has no Ed25519): no `kms:Sign` grant exists on anything related to this\n  key. A second secret holds the read-only repo credentials (tickets branch + review remote).\n- **Least-privilege task role**: read exactly the two secrets above; no tickets-branch write\n  credential exists anywhere in the deployment; no other AWS permissions.\n- **Deploy + prove**: `terraform apply` via the provided authenticated AWS CLI; seed the key\n  secret; then a live integrity check — a SigV4-signed job round-trip against the deployed\n  endpoint (submit → poll → terminal status), plus an UNSIGNED request asserted rejected\n  (401/403 at API Gateway).\n\n## Scope\n- In: Terraform, ECR image build/push, secret seeding procedure (documented, key generated\n  locally with `ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -N \"\"` and stored only in Secrets Manager), the real\n  deploy, the live round-trip evidence, and pinning the deployed environment's public key +\n  `env_id` into `.rebar/trusted_environments.yaml`.\n- Out: the service code and Dockerfile (sibling story); any change to rebar library code; the\n  merge-gate consumer (shipped, 4214).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `infra/opcert/` Terraform declares: API Gateway HTTP API + IAM SigV4 authorizer restricted\n      to a named admin role over TLS; an ECS Fargate service (desired_count=1) on the\n      `Dockerfile.opcert` image; the Ed25519 key in Secrets Manager encrypted by a KMS CMK; and a\n      least-privilege task role. A test asserts the IaC files declare these AND contain NO\n      `kms:Sign` grant and NO tickets-branch write credential.\n- [ ] `terraform validate` (and `terraform plan` against the provided account) succeed; a test or\n      CI step asserts `terraform fmt -check` + `validate` pass.\n- [ ] The deployed environment's public key and `env_id` are pinned in\n      `.rebar/trusted_environments.yaml` (with `added_at_commit` per the epic's era protocol); a\n      test asserts the entry parses and the `env_id` matches the task definition's\n      `REBAR_OPCERT_ENV_ID`.\n- [ ] [operator-attested] The service is deployed from `infra/opcert/` via the authenticated AWS\n      CLI and a live SigV4-signed job round-trip succeeds while an unsigned request is rejected —\n      evidence: a comment recording the `terraform apply` outputs (API endpoint, task/stack\n      identifiers) and the captured round-trip request/response + rejection.","id":"76d2-00c3-88e8-4654","parent_id":"6d0d-7580-e18f-48c3","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"op-cert: AWS IaC + deploy of the trusted gate service + live authenticated integrity test"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783997824956038001,"uuid":"c437a0c6-437d-4853-b711-168fb14b7d0a"}